member.example:
This sample shows how to call GetScenarioRunAsync and parse the result.

TokenCredential credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
ScenarioRunsClient client = new ScenarioRunsClient(Guid.Parse("73f411fe-4f43-4b4b-9cbd-6828d8f4cf9a"), credential);

Response response = await client.GetScenarioRunAsync("<resourceGroupName>", "<workspaceName>", "<scenarioName>", "<runId>", null);

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.ToString());

This sample shows how to call GetScenarioRunAsync with all parameters and parse the result.

TokenCredential credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
ScenarioRunsClient client = new ScenarioRunsClient(Guid.Parse("73f411fe-4f43-4b4b-9cbd-6828d8f4cf9a"), credential);

Response response = await client.GetScenarioRunAsync("<resourceGroupName>", "<workspaceName>", "<scenarioName>", "<runId>", null);

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("properties").GetProperty("workspaceName").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("properties").GetProperty("scenarioName").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("properties").GetProperty("scenarioConfigurationName").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("properties").GetProperty("managedIdentityPrincipalId").ToString());
